'''Akosua''' yɛ a edin a wɔde to mmaa a wɔ woo wɔn kwasiada <ref>(PDF) The Sociolinguistic of Akan Personal Names (researchgate.net)</ref> <ref>Akan names and their meanings - YEN.COM.GH</ref>. Afoforo dwen sɛ Asantefoɔ  na ɛtɔ saa din yi nanso, saa adeyɛ yi yɛ nea ɛkɔ so wɔ akanfoɔ nyinyaa  (akanfoɔ  ne Asantefoɔ, Akuapemfoɔ, Akyemfoɔ, Fantefoɔ) a wodi ammerɛ so. Onipa biara wɔ su ne nneyɛe bi a ɛda adi wɔ da wɔde woo no. Akosua mmerane ne Dampo a n'asekyerɛ ne nea ne  ho yɛ hare. Enti, ɔbaa biara a wɔ woo no kwasiada no yɛ nea ɛse sɛ ne ho yɛ hare wɔ bibiara mu<ref>https://www.researchgate.net/publication/239815297_The_Sociolinguistic_of_Akan_Personal_Names</ref>.

== Farebae ne nkyerɛase ==
Wɔ Akanfoɔ amammerɛ mu no, wonya din a wɔde to da biara no firii wɔn ahoni  hɔ. Wonyaa edin Akosua firii Ahoni a ne hɔ twa a ɛyɛ Kwasiada no ho <ref>'Day born names’ in Dagbani, Ewe and Fante (ghanaweb.com)</ref><ref>https://www.modernghana.com/lifestyle/8691/the-akan-day-names-and-their-embedded-ancient-symb.html</ref>. Mmaa a wɔ woo wɔn kwasiada no yɛ nea wɔyɛ akandifo wɔ wɔn mpɔtam anaa obue kwan. Wɔyɛ mfeefeemu na won ani tumi gye nneɛma a ɛho hia ho <ref>The Akan Day Names and Their Embedded Ancient Symbolism (modernghana.com)</ref><ref>(PDF) The Sociolinguistic of Akan Personal Names (researchgate.net)</ref>.

== Mmaa ahorɔw ==
Sɛnea wɔkyerɛw Edin a wɔde to nna wɔ Ghanaman mu no gu ahorɔw .Eyi te saa esiane akuo ahorɔw a ɛwɔ akanfoɔ mu no ni. Akanman kuo biara wɔ sɛnea wɔkyerɛw edin no, anaa nsonsonoeɛ nnim. Akuapemfoɔ  ne Asantefoɔ kyerɛw Akosua, na Mfantefoɔ kyerɛw no Esi.

== Marima ==
Wɔ Akanfoɔ ne afoforo ammmerɛ a ɛwɔ Ghanaman mu no, nna din a wɔto yɛ nea ɛba mienu; mmaa ne mmaraima. Edin a wɔde to ɔbabirima a wɔ woo no Kwasiada no ne Kwasi anaa akwasi.

== Atitriw a wokura saa Edin no ==
Ghanafo mma ahorɔw pii no ara kura wɔn amammerɛ din na afei nso, abrɔfo anaa Akristofoɔ din. Atitriw a wokuara saa din no bi ne;

* Akosua Addae Amoo Ghanani Agodie mu nsɛmkyerɛwni
* Akosua Gyamama Busia  Ghanani siniyɛfo
* Akosua Serwaa Ghanaiani Mirikatuni
* Akosua Frema Osei Opare Ghanani Amanyɔni
